title: Maryland tops Alabama in 2OT, heads to Sweet 16
description: Sarah Te-Biasu made a tying 3-pointer in the fourth quarter, then scored eight of her 26 points in the second overtime to help fourth-seeded Maryland outlast fifth-seeded Alabama 111-108 on Monday to advance to the Sweet 16 of the women's NCAA Tournament.

title: Mavericks star Davis to make return vs. Nets
description: Dallas Mavericks star Anthony Davis -- who has been out since Feb. 8 with an adductor strain -- will return Monday night against the Brooklyn Nets.
author: Shams Charania

title: 'England show Tuchel's search for thrills will be no quick fix'
description: England's dull victory over Latvia shows new head coach Thomas Tuchel's search for thrills is no easy task, says chief football writer Phil McNulty.

title: Raducanu powers into Miami Open quarter-finals
description: Emma Raducanu is through to her first WTA 1,000 quarter-final after a blistering straight-set win over 17th seed Amanda Anisimova in Miami.

title: Golden State Warriors jersey history - No. 8 - De'Anthony Melton (2024)
description: During his time suiting up for the Warriors, Melton wore only jersey No. 8 and put up 10.3 points, 3.3 rebounds, 2.8 assists, and 1.2 steals per game.

title: OKC Thunder jersey history No. 22 - Bill Hanzlik (1980-82)
description: During his time suiting up for the Sonics, Hanzlik wore only jersey No. 22 and put up 5.6 points, 2.7 rebounds, and 1.9 assists per game.

title: Hamilton and Leclerc disqualified from Chinese GP
description: Ferrari drivers Lewis Hamilton and Charles Leclerc have been disqualified from the Chinese Grand Prix after their respective cars failed post-race technical checks.

title: Raducanu blitzes past Anisimova to move into last eight in Miami
description: Great Britain's Emma Raducanu produced an imperious display against an ill-tempered Amanda Anisimova to march through to the last eight of the Miami Open.
